        <updateDate>2020-08-27T14:46:39Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill makes permanent the reduction in the adjusted gross income (AGI) threshold that must be exceeded before a taxpayer may claim a deduction amount for medical expenses. The reduction is from 10% to 7.5% of AGI and 5% in any taxable year beginnning in 2020 or 2021.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To amend the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 to reduce the floor on the deduction for medical expenses.</title>
